article.headline: Yale 73, Brown 60
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Greg Mangano scored 18 points and grabbed 11 rebounds as Yale defeated Brown 73-60 Saturday. It was the second consecutive game between the two Ivy League teams. Yale (12-4, 2-0) also defeated the Bears (5-13, 0-2) 68-64 last Saturday. Unlike that game, when the Bulldogs came back from a six-point deficit in the final 3 minutes, they led nearly the entire second half this time. Mangano's free throw broke a 38-38 tie 45 seconds after halftime, and an 8-0 run consisting of layups by Jeremiah Kreisberg, Michael Grace and two by Jesse Pritchard put Yale ahead 54-45 with 13:56 remaining. Reggie Willhite finished with 13 points and Pritchard came off the bench to get nine points and eight rebounds for Yale, which outrebounded Brown 49-31. Austin Morgan contributed 10 points and five assists. Stephen Albrecht scored 23 points to lead Brown, and Sean McGonagill added 11.
